defaultExecutive summary default&#xa0;
defaultNDCS is concerned that Ofsted inspections and its annual report do not sufficiently emphasise the importance of local authority specialist SEN support services for deaf children. 
default&#xa0;
defaultA failure to inspect or scrutinise or even comment on these services sends 
defaulta signal that these services are not important, when many deaf children and their families rely on these services to achieve good outcomes. 
